romo and KYNO New Year s Greetings from a bushel of Boss Jocks Chris Van Camp and Dave Roberts perform some classic scoped Boss radio then Harry Miller takes center stage Following Steve Randall/Reynolds and his comments on QRK turntables we are treated to a rare five minutes of Dale Dorman Dave Jeffries caps the hour Our friend Jim Roberts was producer and narrator Another REELRADIO promo in this hour! We are so pleased! And there are also SIX reportable music performances REELRADIO is also included prominently in the closing credits along with those who helped produce this tribute to KYNO on September 1 2008 [combtn gif] COMMENTS ABOUT PART FOUR KYNO BOSS LOOK BACK MORE GOLDEN GIFTS [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2008 REELRADIO INC');
INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/bdlast08.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Jim Roberts and John Ostlund at KYNO in Fresno for this exclusive recording G2 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 32Kbps (10KHz) PLAY Bill Drake Jim Roberts Last Interview KYNO 2008 (09:23) I think a lot of people don t understand basics [Description by Uncle Ricky] This exhibit is an exclusive REELRADIO composite of 2 segments from Hour 1 and Hour 3 of the KYNO Boss Look Back This interview was broadcast on KYNO AM (1300) in Fresno California on September 1 2008 KJWL FM and KYNO AM Owner John Ostlund and Production Manager Jim Roberts did not know they were recording or broadcasting the last interview with the legendary Bill Drake at the time Drake died of lung cancer on November 29 2008 Jim Roberts says he recorded this interview on August 29 2008 Bill Drake mostly kept to himself in recent years We believe this was the last time he granted an interview [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository MORE GOLDEN GIFTS [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2008 REELRADIO INC');
