INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/bekgb081066.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Jeffrey Leonard long time Boss Angeles resident for this Golden Gift via Don Jennett We hope to present The Jeffrey Leonard Collection soon G2 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 20 7Kbps (10KHz) PLAY Bob Elliot KGB San Diego August 10 1966 (45:48) Actually it s the Bill Wade Show but I like to get my name in there somewhere [Description by Uncle Ricky] This exhibit is UNSCOPED meaning that all the music is included We are required to pay a fee for each listener for all musical performances on this recording Plus we must also pay the cost of Internet bandwidth to deliver it to you We are a user supported organization and if you enjoy this exhibit please say thanks with your support Whether you know him as Bob Elliot (WOR FM KGB) or K O Bayley (WJBK KFRC) here he is filling in for Bill Wade at 136 KGB Boss Radio for San Diego Summer 1966 Ray Charles is featured with a Boss Golden and also for Coca Cola  more evidence that Charles was a giant in mainstream media in the mid 60 s The fidelity of this one varies but it s obvious KGB s microphone was very clean for the most part cleaner than their music in 1966 [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository MORE GOLDEN GIFTS [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2005 REELRADIO INC');
INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/cbwcbsfm061089.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Michael DeMonti for his contribution of the WCBS FM New York 1989 Radio Greats Reunion G2 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 44Kbps (20KHz) PLAY Cousin Brucie WCBS FM Radio Greats Reunion June 10 1989 Part One (01:02:25) Rock n Roll and radio were brand new so we were there right at the beginning of the thing We are required to pay a fee for each listener for all musical performances on this recording We are a user supported organization and if you enjoy this exhibit please say thanks with your support [Description by Uncle Ricky] Cousin Bruce Morrow hosts the first of four hours from the 1989 WCBS FM Radio Greats Reunion Also heard in this hour: Dan Ingram Les Marshak and Lenny Coco Marshak explains how he got his first radio job (at 19) via the WABC Star Search and Scott Muni [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository G2 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 44Kbps (20KHz) PLAY Cousin Brucie WCBS FM Radio Greats Reunion June 10 1989 Part Two (55:51) I am so turned on! We are required to pay a fee for each listener for all musical performances on this recording We are a user supported organization and if you enjoy this exhibit please say thanks with your support [Description by Uncle Ricky] WCBS FM Program Director Joe McCoy and legendary WABC Program Director Rick Sklar join Cousin Brucie Les Marshak and others in this hour of the 1989 Radio Greats Reunion Musically The Genies and The Earls are representative of the fresh 50 s hits in this hour [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository G2 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 44Kbps (20KHz) PLAY Cousin Brucie WCBS FM Radio Greats Reunion June 10 1989 Part Three (57:57) CBS FM today is the station that has personalities They have real air personalities they re people And each one s different We are required to pay a fee for each listener for all musical performances on this recording We are a user supported organization and if you enjoy this exhibit please say thanks with your support [Description by Uncle Ricky] Herb Oscar Anderson joins Bruce Morrow Les Marshak Dan Ingram and Rick Sklar Dan and Bruce and Rick tell several stories and Bruce begins counting down the Top Ten from a 1956 WINS playlist Also included: early airchecks from WINS and WABC (Listen for a couple of great R&B tunes!) [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository G2 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 44Kbps (20KHz) PLAY Cousin Brucie WCBS FM Radio Greats Reunion June 10 1989 Part Four (56:15) Bruce they ARE the story We are required to pay a fee for each listener for all musical performances on this recording We are a user supported organization and if you enjoy this exhibit please say thanks with your support [Description by Uncle Ricky] Herb Oscar Anderson Les Marshak and Cousin Brucie continue the WINS 1956 Countdown and Charlie Greer joins the group in Brucie s fourth hour of the 1989 WCBS FM Radio Greats Reunion along with Bobby Jay and others (Due to technical problems Herb s rendition of You Don t Bring Me Flowers is not included ) [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository MORE GOLDEN GIFTS [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2005 REELRADIO INC');
