INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/wswhb61.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Richard Fatherley (Radio s Revolution and Todd Storz) for this classic recording of WHB! G2 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 32Kbps (10KHz) PLAY Wayne Stitt WHB Kansas City 1961 (08:46) Hi this is Anita Bryant At the tone the perfect combination Wayne Stitt Music and You [Description by Uncle Ricky] REELRADIO is presenting this GOLDEN GIFT from Richard Fatherley (Radio s Revolution and Todd Storz) with a note that The Library Of American Broadcasting named WHB owner and Top40 Pioneer Todd Storz as one of their Giants of Broadcasting on September 15 2004 Picture of Wayne Stitt Wayne Stitt This was apparently taken from a recording off the board without processing and you ll hear some serious clipping a few times on Wayne Stitt s microphone But what tremendous energy for a midday show from 1961! Despite the technical flaws it s amazing to hear the Storz Top 40 format from this year Jingles galore including a Daddy parody we ve not heard before Stitt could have set L A or N Y on fire on any format and station hot enough for his rapid patter and enthusiasm Please note that this gentleman was already a properly speaking middle aged adult who wore a tie for his publicity photo  and his boss couldn t own any other stations in the market Original editing for this presentation: Dave Brock AudioVision Overland Park Kansas [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository MORE GOLDEN GIFTS [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2015 REELRADIO INC');
INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/dicbs89.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Michael DeMonti for his high fidelity recordings of the WCBS FM Rock and Roll Radio Greats Reunion Weekend from 1989 G2 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 32Kbps (15KHz) PLAY Dan Ingram WCBS FM Rock And Roll Radio Greats Weekend 1989 (02:53:47) I remember lost art a long time ago Where is he now? Has anyone ever found him? [Description by Uncle Ricky] A scoped version of the WCBS FM Rock and Roll Radio Greats Reunion was contributed to REELRADIO by The Dan Haber Collection in December 1996 To celebrate Dan Ingram s 70th birthday (September 7 2004) we presented this UNSCOPED version of his entire 3 hour shift on the 1989 Radio Greats Weekend (A few minutes of news are not included ) Because the original contribution was encoded in Real Audio 3 0 this exhibit featured much higher fidelity Also of particular interest is an appearance of the late Chuck Leonard who talks with Dan beginning at 2:27:30 This temporary exhibit was available only through September 5 11 2004 [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository MORE GOLDEN GIFTS [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2004 REELRADIO INC');
INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/ddrkfrc080974.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to David Gordon for this excellent recording of Doctor Don Rose and KFRC FM G2 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 32Kbps (12KHz) PLAY Dr Don Rose KFRC San Francisco August 9 1974 (57:12) Got some new terminology to get used to today President Ford play This Exhibit SCOPED (29:13) SCOPED If all you want is the jings and the jock and the news and the spots this version s for you! Please remember that in addition to music licensing fees for the UNSCOPED version there are bandwidth and hardware costs for this SCOPED version and anything streamed from REELRADIO We welcome your support [Description by Uncle Ricky] Doctor Don Rose and newsman Jack Hines are heard on KFRC San Francisco on Friday August 9 1974 The big story of the day: President Richard M Nixon had officially resigned his office Contributor David Gordon made this unscoped recording from KFRC FM which was simulcasting the AM until 8 that morning At the end of the aircheck you ll hear a few seconds of the FM oldies format Dr Don Rose passed away on March 29 2005 [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository MORE GOLDEN GIFTS [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2004 REELRADIO INC');
INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/fjkbox112166.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Gary S McBrayer for this GOLDEN GIFT believed to have been originally recorded by Repository contributor Jay Marks G2 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 32Kbps (10KHz) PLAY Frank Jolle KBOX Dallas TX November 21 1966 (07:12) I have premature gray hair so I had my hair died blue so no one would even notice it [Description by contributor Gary S McBrayer] As illustrated by this check Frank Jolle was a crazy man at night on KBOX I think he pretty much did what he wanted during his show regardless of the prescribed format Of note on this check taken between 10 and 11 pm on November 21 1966 is the number of local & regional hits that get airplay  records by These Few The Exotics Jade of Stone and Dana Rollin s version of Winchester Cathedral At this time Dallas had become a rather hot market for regional breakouts with KBOX KLIF and the Sump n Else Dance Show all taking chances and giving local and regional bands airtime Also of interest to Dallasites is Frank s announcement of an eyewitness spotting of the Lady of The Lake a legendary ghost that supposedly haunted the White Rock Lake area of Dallas [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository MORE GOLDEN GIFTS [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2006 REELRADIO INC');
INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/mdz100.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Anita Bonita for this STEREO exhibit from Z 100 (WHTZ FM) in New York City G2 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 96Kbps (16KHz STEREO) PLAY Micky Dolenz Z100 WHTZ New York July 25 1986 (18:09) he doesn t do you know none of the Monkees do any radio [Description by Anita Bonita] Welcome To My Nightmare: in the middle of all the usual craziness of Z 100 Morning Zoo operations just as the producer (yours truly) is trying to sneak in a special surprise guest (and cake!) for the anniversary of the PD/Zoomeister s birth the PD is excitedly announcing the arrival of a core artist s eagerly awaited brand new record along with all the requisite label weasels who must be stroked accordingly The main voices you hear at the start: Micky Dolenz Scott Shannon then sidekick Jack Murphy and John Mr Leonard Rio In the background you hear the laughter of newsperson Claire Stevens (later heard reading the birthday list and horriblescopes ) public service director John Bell and me (when I wasn t scrambling to get stuff done in production) In the end Micky got to sing Birthday and present the cake to Scott Billy Joel s A Matter of Trust got carted up and made its major league debut and I lived to tell the story 18 years later : ) [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository MORE GOLDEN GIFTS [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2004 REELRADIO INC');
INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/wnaprc70.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Dan Kincaid for his contribution of The WNAP History Of Rock And Roll recorded in Indianapolis in April and August of 1970 This exhibit features a portion of that special dedicated to Ray Charles G2 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 32Kbps (14KHz) PLAY WNAP Indianapolis Salutes Ray Charles 1970 (16:33) If I had to take any records with me I d probably just say forget the whole thing I don t want to be bothered [Description by Uncle Ricky] Picture This special REELRADIO feature was composited from three different sources It begins with a portion of The History of Rock and Roll as broadcast in Indianapolis on WNAP in August of 1970 Contributor Dan Kincaid wrote that his recording was on quarter track reel at 3 3/4 IPS When Dan contributed it to REELRADIO in 1999 he transferred the reels to HI FI VHS A montage of Ray Charles Music comments from Ray Charles three of his classic hits and narration are included Who narrated Picture of an older Ray Charles in a tuxedo this version of the legendary special? If WNAP was not an RKO station was it one of the first non RKO stations to broadcast this special? The reverb you ll hear on this part of the feature is the authentic WNAP reverb in use at the time of broadcast The HORR segment is followed by a brief excerpt of ABC Radio News from June 10 2004 the date of Charles passing You ll hear a comment from Stevie Wonder followed by a rendition of America The Beautiful performed by The Genius  Ray Charles [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository MORE GOLDEN GIFTS [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2004 REELRADIO INC');
INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/bewor68.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Wayne Scott of Great Scott Productions of Ridgeland MS for yet another great aircheck of The Big Town Sound G2 5 0 compatible STEREO TOP STREAM 105Kbps (16KHz STEREO) BROADBAND RECOMMENDED! PLAY Bob Elliot WOR FM New York 1968 (01:12:19) Memories are made of this [Description by Uncle Ricky] WOR FM THE BIG TOWN SOUND Bob Elliot Bob Elliot WOR FM 8PM 12M The late Bob Elliot who was also known as K O Bayley is heard on this very good to excellent stereo recording of The Big Town Sound on WOR FM in January of 1968 Elliot worked at KYNO in Fresno KEWB in Oakland and KBLA in Los Angeles just prior to his time at WOR FM It s original Drake all the way with the big guy himself featured on legendary liners like The Hits Just Keep On Coming and Memories Are Made Of This This is a reminder that REELRADIO must pay license and performance fees for the music featured on this unscoped aircheck Our organization is user supported Please contribute ten dollars (or more) now and enjoy this exhibit! And as Bob says Be ready with your tweeters and woofers you might hear something you ain t NEVER heard before Me Too! There are some genuine goodies here Million Dollar Music for sure But the recording is not without flaws A short portion of I Thank You was reconstructed and bits of You ve Really Got A Hold On Me never made it to the encoder We also suspect that WOR FM was playing everything from cart A few songs are too tight at the beginning and the stereo phase changed frequently with the program content Still 72 uncut minutes of WOR FM of this vintage in stereo is a near miracle Our thanks again to contributor Wayne Scott [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository MORE GOLDEN GIFTS [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2004 REELRADIO INC');
INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/tmrocksolid.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Anonymous for this exhibit That s our story and we re stickin to it G2 5 0 compatible STREEO TOP STREAM 96 5Kbps [20 KHz STEREO REALAUDIO 8] PLAY TM Rock Solid Demo 1986 (06:34) Here s Rock Solid support for your station s identity [Description by Uncle Ricky] Mr Anonymous contributed this exhibit It was something that his boss cleaned out of his desk and was otherwise going to dumpsterize Mr Anonymous felt better sending it to me than dumping it And it s very nice actually great fidelity for a 1986 cassette KMEL in San Francisco is the featured client Again REELRADIO (with the help of Mr Anonymous) has rescued some of radio s near refuse  and in STEREO no less This one s at 96Kbps and sounds particularly HOT! [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository MORE GOLDEN GIFTS www reelradio com Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2004 REELRADIO INC');
INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/wmjusaf.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Jack McFarland for these recordings of The Wolfman Jack Show produced for The United States Air Force Wolfman Jack for the United States Air Force Selected Programs Gavin Photo Courtesy Ben Fong Torres G2 5 0 COMPATIBLE TOP STREAM 64Kbps 16 Khz STEREO February 1972 PLAY Wolfman Jack Show USAF February 1972 Volume 6 Show 1 (24:43) PLAY Wolfman Jack Show USAF February 1972 Volume 6 Show 2 (24:45) PLAY Wolfman Jack Show USAF February 1972 Volume 6 Show 3 (24:53) PLAY Wolfman Jack Show USAF February 1972 Volume 6 Show 4 (24:58) Think? (4:01) [combtn gif] All Comments for Wolfman Jack for USAF February 1972 Music licensing and performance fees for every song paid by tax deductible contributions to REELRADIO Inc We welcome your support [rew gif] Repository Headquarters There will be many more exhibits in this Golden Gift Collection from Jack McFarland [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2004 REELRADIO INC');
