INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/wmjusaf.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Jack McFarland for these recordings of The Wolfman Jack Show produced for The United States Air Force Wolfman Jack for the United States Air Force Selected Programs Gavin Photo Courtesy Ben Fong Torres G2 5 0 COMPATIBLE TOP STREAM 64Kbps 16 Khz STEREO February 1972 PLAY Wolfman Jack Show USAF February 1972 Volume 6 Show 1 (24:43) PLAY Wolfman Jack Show USAF February 1972 Volume 6 Show 2 (24:45) PLAY Wolfman Jack Show USAF February 1972 Volume 6 Show 3 (24:53) PLAY Wolfman Jack Show USAF February 1972 Volume 6 Show 4 (24:58) Think? (4:01) [combtn gif] All Comments for Wolfman Jack for USAF February 1972 Music licensing and performance fees for every song paid by tax deductible contributions to REELRADIO Inc We welcome your support [rew gif] Repository Headquarters There will be many more exhibits in this Golden Gift Collection from Jack McFarland [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2004 REELRADIO INC');
INSERT INTO tsearch(url, body) VALUES('//gifts/blwtic123177.html', 'WWW REELRADIO COM GOLDEN GIFT Our thanks to Bob Radil for this stereo Golden Gift! G2 Stereo 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 64 1Kbps (20KHz Stereo) PLAY Bill Lenke Top Hits 1977 WTIC FM Hartford CT 12 31 77 Part One (48:36) What a chest! MUSIC FEES PAID TO PRESENT MUSIC! You bet this treasure is UNSCOPED and you really will hear all those songs you hoped you could forget Or you can enjoy our SCOPED VERSION! PLAY THE SCOPED VERSION (6:21) [Description by Uncle Ricky] Bill Lenke (better known later as Broadway Bill Lee) is featured with #24 through #13 of the WTIC FM Top Hits of 1977 the first annual presentation sponsored by Subway As with contributor Bob Radil s first WTIC exhibit the jingles and presentation are courtesy of the HOT HITS genius of Mike Joseph You will hear an abundance of female pop too long Eagles songs and a couple of goofy disco records And when we say records we mean you can hear the vinyl Plus the music sounds selectively processed so we wouldn t be surprised if scratchy records were transferred to cart But what a great recording! The excessive audio processing is all original and we tried to preserve the accentuated high end too Part Two of this exhibit features WTIC FM s #12 through #1 Hits of 1977 [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository G2 Stereo 5 0 compatible TOP STREAM 64 1Kbps (20KHz Stereo) PLAY Bill Lenke Top Hits 1977 WTIC FM Hartford CT 12 31 77 Part Two (48:05) Taurus and my name is William and I just wanna get tall that s all! MUSIC FEES PAID TO PRESENT MUSIC! You bet this treasure is UNSCOPED and you really will hear all those songs you hoped you could forget Or you can enjoy our SCOPED VERSION! PLAY THE SCOPED VERSION (6:09) [Description by Uncle Ricky] Bill Lenke continues the countdown with #12 through #1 of the WTIC FM Top Hits of 1977 recorded by contributor Bob Radil on December 31 1977 The Floaters join a crew of Pop superstars including the Bee Gees brother Andy Shaun Cassidy and Barbra Streisand on the way to Number One and a New Year A bonanza of ballads and boogie provide plenty of variety for this classic Top 40 Hot Hits presentation on 96 TIX [combtn gif] [rew gif] Return to the Repository MORE GOLDEN GIFTS [wwwrrcom gif] Reel Top 40 Radio Repository ©1996 2007 REELRADIO INC');
